outputs.description: By the end of 2019, over 500,000 people in the five UNICEF supported focus districts have improved availability of and increaseddemand for high impact maternal, new-born and child health interventions.

By 2019, people  living in 5 target districts have access to improved water and sanitation services and are practicing safe hygienebehaviours (Target - 15,000 rural people with access to water, 90,000 with access to sanitation and 15 Health Posts with WASHfacilities)
By 2019, 20,000 boys and 20,000 girls from 200 schools  benefit from improved, child-friendly, gender appropriate and inclusiveWASH facilities.
By the end of 2019, 25,000 children in 5 districts access and complete quality basic education with improved learning outcomes

By 2019, improved institutional capacity on effective and child-sensitive evidence based planning and budgeting supported by policyanalysis and recommendations, and an enhanced social protection system.
